categories.category_description: Cow milk cheeses are as varied and rich as the producers who make them around the world. Starting with a base of rich, mild cow's milk, cheesemakers then let their imaginations lose to create cheeses that can be creamy and sweet, hard and salty, and everything in between

products.name: Cheese Lapis
products.category_description: Cellars at Jasper Hill's master cheesemaker, Mateo Kehler, provides his expertise and his cheese cave for 60 quarterly wheels of this special-selected cave-matured 12-month-old clothbound cheddar. Kehler's climate-controlled caves and years of knowledge transform Cabot's cows' milk wheels into a things of beauty, full of sharp caramel notes.

products.name: Pickwick Cheddar with Caramelised Onion
products.description: This soft cheese made from goat's milk is a marriage of chèvre and brie that's an approachable variation for soft-cheese lovers. Produced in the beautiful countryside of the Périgord region of France, the Pico Affiné boasts aromatics of fresh hay with a slightly tangy taste and earthy flavor. We think it pairs best with a glass of fruit-forward sparkling white wine.

products.name: Ash Goat Pyramid 'Janier'
products.description: This award-winning sheep and cow's milk cheese is made thanks to the combined efforts of Old Chatham's sheep and their neighbor's BGH-free cows. Named for owner Nancy Clark, this cheese is a delightful addition to a cheese plate and goes well in salads or wrapped up in phyllo sheets.

products.name: Pecorino Romano
products.description: This traditional soft cheese is made from cow's milk in the Burgundy region of France. Its creamy texture, full flavor, and truffle taste make it an approachable and versatile cheese that can hold its own on any cheeseboard. Pair with a chardonnay or rosé and enjoy with apple slices, grapes, nuts, and crackers.

products.name: Fine Fleur de Celles
products.description: Little Hosmer is a pasteurized soft cheese with a bloomy rind. The paste is soft and supple, but not runny. (from Cellars at Jasper Hill)

products.name: Gouda with Truffles
products.description: Aged six months, FreshDirect Sharp Cheddar Cheese is naturally lactose free, gluten-free and has a bold, rich flavor. It's smooth and creamy, making it perfect for snacking and melting in your favorite recipes.

products.name: Black Summer Truffle Chevre
products.description: A game-changing cheese! Aged 6-9 months, this goat gouda from Holland exudes a delightful caramel aroma and buttery taste. To ensure a fuller flavor, the wheels are aged in caves with higher-than-normal ambient temperatures. It pairs beautifully with mellow white wines or slightly sweet amber ales.

products.name: Wensleydale with Cranberries
products.description: Produced in Holland exclusively for the Cypress Grove Dairy in California, Midnight Moon® is the delicious result of the collaboration between Dutch cheesemakers and Cypress Grove founder Mary Keehn. A goat's milk tribute to gouda, this delightful cheese is crumbly, sweet, nutty and grassy. Definitely a cheese to savor on its own, but if you must embellish, try it broken into chunks and spread with just a touch of white fig spread.

products.name: Snowdonia Amber Mist Cheddar with Whisky
products.description: Young Beemster Gouda studded with genuine truffles and no artificial flavors. Rich, nutty, and earthy with a smooth, buttery texture. (from Beemster)

products.name: Gouda with Caramel
products.description: Beemster Farmers' Choice is the most consumed cheese in the Netherlands! This is a great crowd-pleaser because it's creamy and buttery, and at the same time, the 6-months age gives it that bit of tanginess on the finish and some complexity. A beautiful golden yellow interior, smooth and semi-firm. Beemster Farmers' Choice is a perfect introduction to Gouda-style cheeses for the newbie, and the connoisseur will love the classic flavor. (from Beemster)
